The read trace shows `nn` is referenced before it's defined (it's defined after the trace). Let me fix the trace placement:

{
  "analysis": "The read trace references `nn` which is defined later. The trace was placed before the read happens. The trace at position before read can't show result. The earlier trace (trace3) showed reads work. The issue is the directory read returns 20224 bytes but numlumps*16 = 1264*16 = 20224 - correct! So directory IS read. The problem must be in how lumpinfo is stored in memory. Let me move the read trace after the read and check the data written to memory.",
  "plan": "Fix trace to show result after read, and verify the directory data is correctly written to guest memory.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "python3 << 'PYEOF'\nwith open('/app/vm.js','r') as f: c=f.read()\n# Move trace after read completes - replace the broken trace\nc = c.replace(\n    \"if(e._traced<20){console.error('R fd='+a0+' p='+e.p+' n='+a2+' res='+nn);e._traced++;}\",\n    \"\"\n)\n# Add trace after the read in case 0\nc = c.replace(\n    \"e.p += nn; R[2] = nn; return; }\",\n    \"e.p += nn; R[2] = nn; if(a0>=3){if(!e._tc)e._tc=0;if(e._tc<20){console.error('R fd='+a0+' from='+(e.p-nn)+' n='+a2+' got='+nn+' dst=0x'+a1.toString(16)+' b0='+r8(a1)+' b4='+r8(a1+4));e._tc++;}} return; }\"\n)\nwith open('/app/vm.js','w') as f: f.write(c)\nprint('Fixed')\nPYEOF\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "node -c /app/vm.js && echo OK\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "timeout 15 node vm.js > /tmp/trace5.txt 2>&1; grep -aE '^R fd=|Z_Malloc size' /tmp/trace5.txt | head -10\n",
      "duration": 20.0
    }
  ]
